  73,20,"Surely your Lord knows that you ňĻO Prophetňļ stand ňĻin prayerňļ for nearly two-thirds of the night, or ňĻsometimesňļ half of it, or a third, as do some of those with you. Allah ňĻaloneňļ keeps a ňĻpreciseňļ measure of the day and night. He knows that you ňĻbelieversňļ are unable to endure this, and has turned to you in mercy.¬†So recite ňĻin prayerňļ whatever you can from the Quran. He knows that some of you will be sick, some will be travelling throughout the land seeking Allah‚Äôs bounty, and some fighting in the cause of Allah. So recite whatever you can from it. And ňĻcontinue toňļ perform ňĻregularňļ prayers, pay alms-tax, and lend to Allah a good loan.¬†Whatever good you send forth for yourselves, you will find it with Allah far better and more rewarding.¬†And seek Allah‚Äôs forgiveness. Surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
